{"type":"message","id":"34b75a83","parentId":"4d9bd231","timestamp":"2026-03-23T18:55:41.209Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Found it. Now let me read it.","thinkingSignature":"73e4e779abc50aaad5570cb4b46f5bf2422c2dce4d769c34ee78874746e42eb5"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_n7tmmoiudncl_1","name":"read","arguments":{"file_path":"C:\\Users\\Zwmar\\.openclaw\\sandbox\\memory\\session\\pulse_2026-03-23 145511.md"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":772,"output":63,"cacheRead":11844,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":12679,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1774292139195}}
{"type":"message","id":"7e8f41c3","parentId":"34b75a83","timestamp":"2026-03-23T18:55:41.224Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_n7tmmoiudncl_1","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"# Pulse: 2026-03-23 145511\n\n## Applied Mutations\nNo mutations applied this cycle.\nRejected: the (missing)\n\n## LLM Response\n<think>\r\nLooking at the current state, I need to advance the Phase 1 goal focused on the COMPRESSION-CAUSAL DUALITY insight and the TIC (Temporal Invariance Compression) experiment. The pending action is:\r\n\r\n- Implement TIC classifier on `logs/pulse_*.md` files\r\n- Measure invariant/variant classification accuracy\r\n- Predict next pulse content from invariants\r\n- Validate against success criteria (>70%, >60%)\r\n\r\nThe next action should be implementing the TIC classifier. Let me create a concrete implementation file that:\r\n1. Loads recent pulse logs\r\n2. Classifies content as invariant (persistent across sessions) vs variant (session-specific)\r\n3. Uses the invariants to predict next pulse content\r\n4. Measures accuracy against the success criteria\r\n\r\nI'll create a Python script `scripts/tic_classifier.py` that implements this.\r\n</think>\r\n\r\n### OBSERVATION\r\nThe COMPRESSION-CAUSAL DUALITY insight reveals that finding invariant structure IS causal discovery. The TIC (Temporal Invariance Compression) experiment is the next critical step to validate this hypothesis against the >70% classification and >60% prediction success criteria.\r\n\r\n### ACTION\r\nCreate TIC classifier implementation that analyzes pulse logs, identifies invariant vs variant content, and measures prediction accuracy against success criteria.\r\n\r\n### MUTATION\r\n`\r\nold_text: (new file)\r\nnew_text: #!/usr/bin/env python3\r\n\"\"\"\r\nTIC (Temporal Invariance Compression) Classifier\r\nPhase 1 experiment: Test compression-causal duality hypothesis\r\n\r\nHypothesis: Causal structure IS invariant structure\r\n- Invariant content = persistent across sessions = causal factors\r\n- Variant content = session-specific = noise/exogenous\r\n\r\nSuccess criteria:\r\n- >70% invariant/variant classification accuracy\r\n- >60% next-pulse prediction accuracy\r\n\"\"\"\r\n\r\nimport re\r\nimport os\r\nfrom pathlib import Path\r\nfrom collections import Counter\r\n\r\nLOGS_DIR = Path(\"logs\")\r\nMIN_PULSES = 5  # Minimum pulses for analysis\r\n\r\n\r\ndef load_pulse_logs(n_recent=20):\r\n    \"\"\"Load the n most recent pulse log files.\"\"\"\r\n    pulse_files = sorted(LOGS_DIR.glob(\"pulse_*.md\"), reverse=True)[:n_recent]\r\n    pulses = []\r\n    for f in pulse_files:\r\n        content = f.read_text()\r\n        pulses.append({\r\n            'file': f.name,\r\n            'content': content,\r\n            'lines': content.split('\\n')\r\n        })\r\n    return pulses\r\n\r\n\r\ndef extract_content_sections(pulse):\r\n    \"\"\"Extract distinct content sections from a pulse log.\"\"\"\r\n    sections = {\r\n        'goals': [],\r\n        'insights': [],\r\n        'actions': [],\r\n        'notes': []\r\n    }\r\n    \r\n    current_section = None\r\n    for line in pulse['lines']:\r\n        line_lower = line.lower().strip()\r\n        if line_lower.startswith('## '):\r\n            if 'goal' in line_lower:\r\n                current_section = 'goals'\r\n            elif 'insight' in line_lower or 'key' in line_lower:\r\n                current_section = 'insights'\r\n            elif 'action' in line_lower:\r\n                current_section = 'actions'\r\n            elif 'note' in line_lower:\r\n                current_section = 'notes'\r\n            else:\r\n                current_section = None\r\n        elif current_section and line.strip() and not line.strip().startswith('#'):\r\n            sections[current_section].append(line.strip())\r\n    \r\n    return sections\r\n\r\n\r\ndef compute_invariant_score(term, all_pulses):\r\n    \"\"\"Score how invariant a term is across all pulses (0-1).\"\"\"\r\n    presence_count = sum(1 for p in all_pulses if term.lower() in p['content'].lower())\r\n    return presence_count / len(all_pulses)\r\n\r\n\r\ndef classify_pulse_content(pulse, all_pulses, threshold=0.6):\r\n    \"\"\"Classify each content item as invariant or variant.\"\"\"\r\n    sections = extract_content_sections(pulse)\r\n    classified = {'invariant': [], 'variant': []}\r\n    \r\n    for section_name, items in sections.items():\r\n        for item in items:\r\n            # Extract key terms (simple tokenization)\r\n            words = re.findall(r'\\b[a-z]{3,}\\b', item.lower())\r\n            if not words:\r\n                continue\r\n            \r\n            # Compute average invariant score across terms\r\n            scores = [compute_invariant_score(w, all_pulses) for w in words]\r\n            avg_score = sum(scores) / len(scores)\r\n            \r\n            classification = 'invariant' if avg_score >= threshold else 'variant'\r\n            classified[classification].append({\r\n                'text': item[:80],\r\n                'score': round(avg_score, 3),\r\n                'section': section_name\r\n            })\r\n    \r\n    return classified\r\n\r\n\r\ndef predict_next_pulse(prior_pulses):\r\n    \"\"\"Predict what the next pulse should contain based on invariants.\"\"\"\r\n    # Collect all invariant terms from prior pulses\r\n    all_invariants = Counter()\r\n    \r\n    for pulse in prior_pulses:\r\n        classified = classify_pulse_content(pulse, prior_pulses)\r\n        for item in classified['invariant']:\r\n            words = re.findall(r'\\b[a-z]{3,}\\b', item['text'].lower())\r\n            all_invariants.update(words)\r\n    \r\n    # Top invariants are predicted to persist\r\n    top_invariants = [term for term, count in all_invariants.most_common(15)]\r\n    return top_invariants\r\n\r\n\r\ndef measure_prediction_accuracy(prediction, actual_pulse):\r\n    \"\"\"Measure how well prediction matches actual next pulse.\"\"\"\r\n    actual_lower = actual_pulse['content'].lower()\r\n    matched = sum(1 for term in prediction if term in actual_lower)\r\n    return matched / len(prediction) if prediction else 0\r\n\r\n\r\ndef run_tic_experiment():\r\n    \"\"\"Run the full TIC experiment.\"\"\"\r\n    print(\"=\" * 60)\r\n    print(\"TIC (Temporal Invariance Compression) Experiment\n\n## For Next Instantiation\n- Proposed mutations waiting: 1\n- Completed at: 2026-03-23 14:55:35\r\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1774292141222}}
